    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Following review of all 13 credibility factors, the assessment team determined that the overall credibility package is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision. While several factors achieved levels below their required gradations — most notably model form (achieved 2, required 4) and validation relevance (achieved 3, required 5) — compensating evidence from the Monte Carlo UQ, high test condition fidelity, and direct QoI measurement supports a conditional acceptance. The team notes that the structured acceptanceCriteria record for the Relevance of the validation activities to the COU factor was not filed, representing a documentation gap that should be remediated prior to final submission. The decision is Accepted with the recommendation that the acceptanceCriteria gap for validation relevance be resolved in the next assessment cycle.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
